"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-europe-2024-07-29-olympic-opening-ceremony-director-claims-drag-last-supper-not-inspired-by-bible\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The artistic director of the LBGT-themed Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony has claimed he did not intend to portray the Last Supper after an apparent parody of the Biblical event drew outrage from Christians across the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 41, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 72, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9798557283861632, \"rank\": 0.0191101620562689, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.5687140680541727, \"rank\": 0.4453736073383637, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The artistic director\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 21}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 129}, {\"ngram\": \"an apparent parody\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 154}, {\"ngram\": \"the Biblical event\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 176}, {\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 182, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the Olympic Opening Ceremony, denied on Sunday that he was not \\\"inspired\\\" by the Last Supper, despite the striking similarities between the Leonardo da Vinci depiction of the Jesus Christ's Last Supper with his 12 Apostles and the drag queen tableau shown at the opening of the Paris games.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999972407067031, \"rank\": 2.3695580298317764e-06, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9798557283861632, \"rank\": 0.0191101620562689, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3415404791515896e-16, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}, {\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8809898923388976e-18, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999995015160826, \"rank\": 4.98483878029874e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.535849598503892e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artistic director\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"the striking similarities\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"his 12 Apostles\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag queen tableau\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 513}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You will never find in me any desire to mock, or to denigrate anything.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any desire\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to do a ceremony that repairs, that reconciles, that reaffirms the values of our Republic,\\\" Jolly said in commentsreportedbyLe Figaro.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 711}, {\"ngram\": \"our Republic\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"commentsreportedbyLe Figaro\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French artistic director maintained that the Last Supper was \\\"not my inspiration,\\\" saying: \\\"I think it was quite clear, there is Dionysus who arrives on this table.\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6205355370526503e-17, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The French artistic director\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"my inspiration\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"this table\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is there, why?\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because he is the god of the festival\\u2026 of wine, and father of Sequana, the goddess connected to the river.\\\"\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"the festival\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"father\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"the goddess\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1043}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The idea was rather to make a great pagan festival linked to the gods of Olympus,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999999994461177, \"rank\": 5.526683803734534e-10, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"a great pagan festival\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"the gods\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly also claimed that he did not intend to celebrate political violence by showing a decapitated Marie-Antoinette, arguing that there was no \\\"glorification of this instrument of death that was the guillotine.\\\"\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.706073466510198e-34, \"text\": \"Marie-Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"political violence\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"no \\\"glorification\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"this instrument\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"the guillotine\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we use our work to regenerate\\u2026 division, hatred\\u2026 and that it continues to progress, when I believe that we have made a little peace\\u2026 then it would be a great shame,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our work\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"division\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"hatred\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"a little peace\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"a great shame\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The comments from Jolly came as the organisers of the Opening Ceremonyissuedessentially a non-apology, saying: \\\"If people have taken any offence, we are of course really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The comments\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonyissuedessentially\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"any offence\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The apparent mockery of the Christian religion drew fierce backlash throughout the world, with Catholic Bishop Robert Barrondescribingthe drag queen scene as \\\"gross, flippant mockery\\\" of a \\\"very central moment in Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9537183349687757, \"rank\": 0.048527603312131525, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999229203, \"rank\": 6.829558968330122e-11, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9996389778189334, \"rank\": 0.00036115252776630044, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8020422519435494, \"rank\": 0.24681591576055592, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The apparent mockery\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"fierce backlash\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"gross, flippant mockery\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngr